content: The Korean Memorial Cemetery is considered to be the best place to see cherry blossoms in Seoul, burying modern Korean historical and political figures. It is worth seeing that there are cemeteries of former presidents and generals, not far from the metro. There are also exhibitions of the memorial hall of Korean soldiers killed in battle. The cemeteries are free to visit, as well as guards.
If you go in spring, you can see the beautiful appearance of the cherry blossoms. Parking is free and if you bring a simple lunch box and enjoy a picnic, you will be very satisfied. I recommend it!
